The International Mathematical Kangaroo Contest (link: http://www.kangur-mat.pl/) is aimed at elementary, middle and high school students, from grade three in elementary school to graduating classes in high schools and technical schools. It is played in six categories, which include the following grades:
* Beginner category - grades 2 of elementary schools;
* Toddler - grades 3 and 4 of elementary schools;
* Benjamin - grades 5 and 6 of elementary schools;
* Cadet - grades I and II of junior high schools;
* Junior - grades III of middle schools, I of high schools and technical schools;
* Student - grades II and III of high schools and technical schools and IV of technical schools.

The competition is a one-time test. The tasks and the deadline are set by the international commission. 75 minutes are allocated for solving the test.
